h2 Examples
p.-text
  | To render a number input, apply the classes <code>a-input</code> to an <code>input type="number"</code>.
  | For proper styling, number inputs must be wrapped in an <code>m-input__wrapper</code> div with two buttons.

h3 Base

.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-form__item.-row
      .m-input__wrapper
        input.a-input(type="number", value="0", aria-label="Input Label")
        button(aria-label='decrease')
        button(aria-label='increase')
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-form__item -row">
      <div class="m-input__wrapper">
        <input type="number" class="a-input" value="0" aria-label="Input Label">
        <button aria-label="Decrease"></button>
        <button aria-label="Increase"></button>
      </div>
    </div>

